photo.description: La cathédrale de Reims (XIIIème siècle) est un chef d'oeuvre de l'art gothique. Consacrée à la Vierge Marie, elle a été achevée au XIVème siècle. La galerie des rois sur la façade on voit Clovis au centre avec sa femme Clotilde. Reims cathedral (XIII century) is a masterpiece of Gothic art.Dedicated to the Virgin Mary, she was completed in the fourteenth century.The gallery of kings on the front we see Clovis at the center with his wife Clotilde.

photo.description: We stopped in Reims for a night on our way to Paris to visit yet another Notre Dame Cathedral. We also visited the adjacent palace, which had an interesting art exhibit featuring some artists I am familiar with, such as Carsten Nicolai, which was a bit of a surprise.
